{
  "stem": "95.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I did not know about the examination camps.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Every night-- even when I knew about extermination camps-- every night before I close my eyes, I would pray to God to save everybody in my family.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I would just go from my father down to the last nephew, say, please, save them, like I am safe right now.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Did not obey, but I did that.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "As I said, even when I knew about extermination camps, what they were doing with older people and younger children, by that time I was-- but still, in-- I was hardened, but still in my brain, in some where, it-- maybe not.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Maybe they'll escape like I'm escaping.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Now, 19 months later, we evacuated in Ottmuth, because it's going to be an English prisoner of war stalag.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And we are all sent-- all the 150 people-- to a-- to a satellite of Auschwitz called Blechhammer.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And there-- it's a big camp, because from 150 people, we are 3,000 in that camp.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Brick walls, which we did not have in Ottmuth.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Electrified barbed wire, which we did not have in Ottmuth.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Guard towers, which we did not have in Ottmuth.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Lots of barracks.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "SS guarding us, which we did not have in Ottmuth.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They were all Wehrmacht people.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "A complete change.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we arrived, we are 150 people in this huge camp. 'Arbeit macht frei,' you know, the-- what they say in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they send us to the-- yes?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I just wanted to ask you-- when they took you from Ottmuth, did they just wake you up one morning and you were gone, or did you have-- were you aware that you were going--",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
